The paper deals with a graph optimization problem and presents a new approximation algorithm. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories related to graph algorithms and optimization. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely categories since they often deal with graph problems. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possibility since the problem involves degree constraints. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also possible categories since the paper discusses the hardness of the problem and the complexity of the algorithm.
